DIRECTORY STUCTURE
==================

The Appscio MPF project contains the following subdirectories:

- GRDF - The G Resource Definition Framework
- MPF - The Media Processing Framework, including sample components
- applications - Applications built on Appscio MPF
- docs - Supporting documentation
- tools - Tools that extend the Appscio MPF


BUILDING MPF
============

To build MPF you will need a recent, 64-bit Linux distribution with the
following prerequisites:

- Apache Ant (http://ant.apache.org)
- ffmpeg version 0.5 or above (can be obtained from http://rpmfusion.org)
- ffmpeg-devel
- gstreamer version 0.10.24 or above
- gstreamer-devel
- gstreamer-ffmpeg
- gstreamer-plugins-base
- gstreamer-plugins-base-devel
- gstreamer-plugins-flumpegdemux
- Java JDK version 1.6.0 or above
- opencv version 1.0.0 or above
- opencv-devel

Once the prerequisites are installed, go to the MPF subdirectory and run:

ant build-all


BUILDING THE GRAILS-MPF-DETECTOR PLUGIN
=======================================

The plugin requires Grails version 1.2.1 (http://grails.org/download/archive/Grails)

To build the plugin for installation in a standalone Grails application, go to
tools/grails-plugins/VideoEventDetect and run:

grails package-plugin

To run the plugin under a test application, go to
tools/grails-plugins/VideoEventDetect/test/projects/MpfDetectorPluginTestbed and run:

grails run-app


BUILDING THE LARGE DATA EVALUATOR APPLICATION
=============================================

Requires Grails version 1.2.1 (http://grails.org/download/archive/Grails)

Go to applications/LDE and run:

grails run-app


